    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1685"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1685">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.114M69/153.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 16, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I have received from the Minister for Foreign Affairs today reply to my various
                    notes concerning our claim of jurisdiction over Captain steamship <hi
                        rend="italic">Texas</hi> and request for surrender.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rockhill</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
